{"id":"8147","name":"Glyph Search","tagline":"I got tired of looking for shortcut icons that I know *are* there","icon":"ios15 c4292093695 g59772","latest":"32756","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<hr>\n<p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è I've been sherlocked! ü•≥üçæ iOS 16 includes a native glyph search! ‚ö†Ô∏è</strong></p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Glyph Search</strong> allows searching for shortcut glyphs (the symbols in the icons) by name in any of the <strong>39 languages</strong> of the Shortcuts app.</p>\n<p>Its result is an scroll-able glyph grid with the searched glyph highlighted by the intersection of a vertical and an horizontal color bands.</p>\n<h2>New version 2.0!</h2>\n<p><strong>Version 2.0.0</strong> updates the glyphs to the iOS 15.4 / macOS 12.3 ones, including folder glyphs, and shows the location of glyphs imitating each device's layout (horizontal for iOS, vertical for macOS; four rows of folder glyphs in iPhones, three rows in iPads).</p>\n<p>iOS 15 loss of performance (relatively to iOS 14) made the original search (made with native actions) crash frequently, and alternative methods were too slow, so <strong>the search is now done with JavaScript</strong>.</p>\n<p>JavaScript's speed also allows significant improvements in the order of the search results and the matched text shown at the end.</p>\n<h4>iPhone landscape</h4>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://atnbueno.com/glyph-search-ios-demo.png\"></p>\n<h4>iPad folder glyphs</h4>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://atnbueno.com/glyph-search-ipados-folders-demo.png\"></p>\n<h4>macOS</h4>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://atnbueno.com/glyph-search-macos-demo.png\"></p>\n<h2>Previous versions</h2>\n<p>Version 1.1.0 improved the final visualization by showing both a zoomed and a general view of the glyphs. Both views are positioned so the scrollbar marks what part of the general view is zoomed above.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.atnbueno.com/glyph-search.png\"></p>\n<p>The glyph images are from a stitched screenshot of a 3x iOS device. All the glyph data is also available in my <a href=\"https://github.com/atnbueno/Shortcuts/tree/main/Glyphs\">Shortcuts repo @ GitHub</a>.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>2.0.0 - April 15, 2022, 4:31 p.m.</strong></p><p>Updated to iOS 15.4 / macOS 12.3 glyphs, including iOS's folder glyphs, and showing the glyphs imitating each device's layout</p>"}